meaning_str.bing:
n. 牙医
网络. 牙科医生；牙科医师；牙医师

牙科医生；牙科医师；牙医师

牙医；牙科医生；口腔医生；牙科诊所

1.en: Nobody shouted at me for parking my bike, but nobody paid me for going to the dentist either.
1.cn: 没有人会在我停自行车时冲我大喊，不过也没有人在我看牙医时还付给我工钱。

2.en: How much did your trip to the dentist cost?
2.cn: 你到牙医那边晃一圈花了多少钱？

3.en: She had an appointment to see the dentist, but chickened out at the last moment.
3.cn: 她约好了要去看牙医，但最后一刻却因胆怯而退缩了。

0.en: Wait, your, your mother is sleeping with your dentist?
0.cn: 你妈和你的牙医上床吗？

1.en: Peppa, George, the dentist will see you now. Hooray. This is Dr. Elephant, the dentist.
1.cn: 佩奇，乔治，轮到你们做检查啦。太好啦！这位是牙医，大象先生。

2.en: George, are your teeth clean like mine? It is George's first visit to the dentist. You both have lovely clean teeth, I am sure the dentist will be very happy.
2.cn: 乔治，你的和我的一样干净吗？这是乔治第一次去看牙医。你们的牙齿又白又干净，我相信牙医会很高兴的。

3.en: All right, then, just shout when you hear the task you want to undertake. Dentist.
3.cn: 好了，听到你想接的任务时就吼一声。看牙医。

4.en: Former dentist. I need a new one now that I know where his hands have been.
4.cn: 前牙医，我要换一个，我知道他的手摸过"什么"了。

5.en: Girls, I want you to meet Mr Gru. He's going to adopt you. And he's a dentist!
5.cn: 姑娘们 来见见格鲁先生。他是来收养你们的，他是牙医哦！

6.en: I'm starting to get a sense of it. Don't worry. I'll take you to the dentist tomorrow.
6.cn: 我已经开始有所体会了，别担心，我明天带你去看牙医。

7.en: We're gonna make this tank so filthy the dentist will have to clean it. Good work!
7.cn: 我们要搞的这个水箱脏到那个牙医不得不清理的地步。干得好!

8.en: Yeah, well, Bernadette's a little under the weather and my mom's kind of under my dentist.
8.cn: 天气转凉，伯纳黛特身体不适，我妈则被我的牙医压在了身下。

9.en: My mom's been kind of an emotional wreck since that dentist she was dating dumped her.
9.cn: 我妈被之前好上的那牙医抛弃之后，心情就落到了谷底，郁郁寡欢。

10.en: Every morning Peppa and George brush their teeth. Today Peppa and George are going to the dentist.
10.cn: 每天早上佩奇和乔治都会刷牙。今天牙医会检查他们的牙齿。

11.en: Howard doesn't make me do his shopping or take him to the dentist or pick up his dry cleaning, right?
11.cn: 霍华德就不会叫我帮他买东西，送他去看牙医，帮他拿干洗的衣服，对吧？

12.en: Now can you show me your teeth? George does not want to show the dentist his teeth. George, open wide, like this.
12.cn: 现在让我来看看你的牙齿？乔治不想让牙医检查牙齿。乔治，张开嘴，像这样。就是这样。

13.en: I saved you a dumpling. Oh, your concern for me is touching. It will serve you well when you take me to the dentist tomorrow.
13.cn: 我给你留了个饺子。你对我的关心真叫人感动，等你明天载我去看牙医我再好好报答你。

14.en: The water jet please, Ms. Rabbit. The dentist uses water to clean Mr. Dinosaur's teeth. The polisher, please, Ms. Rabbit. This would be a bit noisy.
14.cn: 请准备洗牙机。牙医用水来清洁牙齿。请准备抛光机，兔小姐。可能会有点吵哦。

15.en: Peppa and George are at the dentist's waiting for their check-up. Waiting is boring. This magazine's very interesting. It's all about potatoes.
15.cn: 佩奇和乔治来到牙医诊所等着做检查。一直等好无聊啊。这个杂志真的是太有趣了。全都是关于马铃薯的。

16.en: Anyhow, when you guys wake up and smell the sulfur, here's a list of other realtors, and if you need me, I'll be in the office at 9:00, 10:00. I have the dentist.
16.cn: 总之，如果你们能清醒过来闻到硫磺的味道，这是其它地产经纪的名单如果想找我，我九点上班还是十点吧，我要去看牙医。

17.en: I shower twice a day and wash my hands as often as I can. Really? So do I. But you're a dentist. He's nuts.
17.cn: 我每天洗两次澡，洗手无数次。真的？我也是。但你是牙科学生，他只是疯子。

18.en: Maybe you can hold Mr. Dinosaur while the dentist looks at your teeth. Dinosaur. Very please to meet you, Mr. Dinosaur.
18.cn: 或许你可以抱着恐龙先生。恐龙。很高兴见到你，恐龙先生。
